root_causes: Missing entry condition restricting validation to respondents where qCountry = 3081 (Australia).
Validation includes special codes 97, 98, 99 that are not listed in the expected answer set.
instructions: Restrict the validation so it only runs for respondents from Australia. Example SPSS approach: temporary. sel if qCountry = 3081 & (miss(S9AU) or ~any(S9AU,52,53,54,55,56,57,58,59)). list respid, S9AU.
If special codes 97/98/99 are not defined for this question in the survey metadata, remove them from the any() check. If they are valid, document their meanings and keep them in the allowed list.
